>>57728902
I know this is going to basically be a blogpost, but judging by some personal experiments I did, yes in a controlled moderation. I used to drink a large cup everyday except the weekends where I'd suffer headaches and just general exhaustion thanks to the withdraw on saturday, then I'd basically sleep all day Sunday. About 3 years ago I quit drinking coffee completely for about 20 months, with my only caffine intake being the occasional tea about once every few weeks or so if I desperately needed to wake up for something important. As a result my sleep schedule improved for about the first 14 months, where I was sleeping longer and more comfortably. After that though I started to lose sleep and wake up constantly in the middle of the night getting about 4 to 6 hours of sleep every other night. After the aforementioned 20 months I decided to start drinking coffee again. This time though, I only drink if I had a rough sleep and need to work that day, I also stopped using sugar and just drink it with a little creamer. The result is about the same as before I initially quit but I no longer suffer caffine withdraw symptoms and half a small mug is just as effective as the large cup I used to drink since I don't drink it just about every day now.

What you've got so far is quite good. Based on what's already written I'm going to assume you want this first contact to start off a little awkward, and I'm going to assume Åucja is low class/caste. With those assumptions in mind there are a couple tweaks I'd suggest: When Åucja says
>"uh... I never named this thing"
It suggests that naming or even having a designation for their vessels is either unimportant or a very low priority for either her species or her class/caste, which probably reflects on how valued she is in her society. If that is what you're getting at then I'd double down with that line and have it say something like
>"This is Åucja Määttä of the... uh, well... I guess I never named this old boy, did I? Anyways, we're almost at your position."
Then have Anon question who "we" is once he's on board and the initial alien ogling is done and have Åucja nervously explain that she meant her and her ship. Her lonely voyages in space having lead her to think of her vessel as a companion despite it being nameless and not exactly a cruise liner. The other two tweaks I'd suggest are during the scene where Anon strips out from his EVA suit. First, have her watch him remove his gear and have Anon notice her shift awkwardly, move her head like she doesn't know where to look, etc, but have him think that it's because of how bizarre the situation is rather than her being concerned about modesty. This would mirror Anon averting his eyes from her as she strips. Secondly, when we get a description of her appearance I don't think naming the species you're basing her off of is the best way to go about describing her. Go into some detail about her features; the shape of her face, length of her whiskers, colour of her eyes, colours, pattern and texture of her fur. You don't have to get super detailed, just a short paragraph. Aside from those three little things I think you've got a great start here. And if any of my assumption are wrong, ignore me lol
